From ab0345aec345b818c51ecd4d9c6e3682950adf7d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: xylitol <xylitol@localhost>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 19:28:11 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] msm8937-common: switch USB init back to legacy
 android_usb

The kernel builds the legacy G_ANDROID gadget (CONFIG_USB_CONFIGFS is
not set on any moto-msm89xx branch), but commit e8faebe ("Enable USB
configfs and add init script") switched userspace to configfs with no
kernel counterpart. On boot, init.msm.usb.configfs.rc's unconditional
configfs mkdirs re-enter function allocators android.c already claimed
at probe: mtp/accessory fail EBUSY and the second audio_source mkdir
hits a duplicate-sysfs error path ending in BUG_ON in
sysfs_create_file_ns -> kernel panic at ~7s (pstore-confirmed on perry;
configfs.o is built into libcomposite unconditionally in this tree, so
/config/usb_gadget exists even without CONFIG_USB_CONFIGFS).

Mirror official LineageOS 18.1, which shipped booting cedric builds on
this same kernel with the legacy path:
- drop androidboot.usbconfigfs=true from BOARD_KERNEL_CMDLINE
- replace init.msm.usb.configfs.rc with init.mmi.usb.rc, taken verbatim
  from LineageOS/android_device_motorola_msm8937-common lineage-18.1
  (ae102af); it is the pre-e8faebe file minus the unshipped
  vendor.mmi-usb-sh service, and carries the functionfs adb setup
  Android 11 adbd needs (f_ffs/aliases adb, sys.usb.ffs.aio_compat=1)

With the configfs rc gone, nothing sets sys.usb.configfs=1 at boot, so
init.usb.rc's default 0 keeps init on the legacy android_usb path.
---
 BoardConfigCommon.mk                 |   2 +-
 msm8937.mk                           |   2 +-
 rootdir/Android.mk                   |   4 +-
 rootdir/etc/init.mmi.rc              |   3 +-
 rootdir/etc/init.mmi.usb.rc          | 363 +++++++++++++++++++++++++
 rootdir/etc/init.msm.usb.configfs.rc | 386 ---------------------------
 6 files changed, 369 insertions(+), 391 deletions(-)
 create mode 100644 rootdir/etc/init.mmi.usb.rc
 delete mode 100644 rootdir/etc/init.msm.usb.configfs.rc

